<p itemprop="description">Problem management involves identifying, analysing, and resolving the root causes of problems to prevent future incidents and improve service quality and organisational performance.</p>

<div class="proficiency-levels">
    <h2>Proficiency Levels</h2>

    <ol class="skill-levels">
        <li>
            <h3>Awareness</h3>
            <p>You can recognise problems and understand the difference between incidents and underlying problems. You can contribute to problem-solving activities.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Working</h3>
            <p>You can investigate problems using structured approaches, identify potential root causes, and implement solutions under guidance. You can document problems and their resolution.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Practitioner</h3>
            <p>You can lead complex problem investigations, perform root cause analysis, design comprehensive solutions, and establish processes to prevent problem recurrence.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Expert</h3>
            <p>You can establish problem management frameworks and methodologies, lead organisation-wide problem resolution initiatives, and mentor others in advanced problem-solving techniques.</p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</div>

